#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "About Cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit is a web-based graphical interface that enables you to manage most "
"of the administration task from one place by using plugins. You do not need "
"to create credentials for cockpit as by default Cockpit uses the same "
"credentials that you use to login to your server. Cockpit uses APIs that "
"already exist on the system without adding additional layer to your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cockpit enables you to perform the following tasks:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "download container images and run containers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "update the server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "inspect and change network settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "manage user accounts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "view system logs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "create and administer virtual machines"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "inspect and interact with &systemd; services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "use a terminal on a remote server in your web browser"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting Cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit is included in the delivered pre-built images, or can be installed "
"if you are installing your own instances manually. For details regarding the "
"manual installation, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-settings-software\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Though Cockpit is present in the pre-built images by default, the plugin for "
"administration of virtual machines needs to be installed manually. You can "
"do so by installing the <literal>microos-cockpit</literal> pattern as "
"described bellow. Use the command below as well in case Cockpit is not "
"installed on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;transactional-update pkg install -t pattern microos-cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot your machine to switch to the latest snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit's plugins installed from the <literal>microos-cockpit</literal> "
"pattern may differ according to technologies installed on your system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The plugin <literal>Podman containers</literal> is installed only if the "
"<emphasis>Containers Runtime for non-clustered systems</emphasis> patterns "
"are installed on your system. Similarly, the <literal>Virtual Machines</"
"literal> plugin is installed only if the <emphasis>KVM Virtualization Host</"
"emphasis> pattern is installed on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the Cockpit instance is intended to serve as a primary one, you need to "
"enable the cockpit socket in systemd by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After running the command, the server will expose the default "
"<emphasis>9090</emphasis> port. &systemd; will start the <literal>cockpit-"
"ws</literal> that enables you to administer secondary servers from the "
"primary server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you have enabled the firewall, you also must open the firewall for "
"Cockpit as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "And then reload the firewall configuration by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --reload"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can access the Cockpit web interface by opening the following "
"address in your web browser:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "https://<replaceable>IP_ADDRESS_OF_MACHINE</replaceable>:9090"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cockpit authentication"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit enables you to log in directly to each machine that can expose the "
"9090 port. If the port cannot be accessed on the particular machine, you can "
"still use Cockpit to administer the machine by using it as a secondary "
"server. For a procedure of adding a server as secondary, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-adding-servers\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "A limited count of secondary servers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The count of secondary servers that you can administer from one primary "
"session is limited to 20. If you need to administer more servers, add other "
"primary sessions or use another tool for cluster administration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To log in to the primary server, enter your credentials on the Cockpit login "
"page. To log in to secondary servers, there are two options. You can access "
"secondary machines after log in to the primary server, or you can access a "
"secondary machine using the <guimenu>Connect to</guimenu> field on the login "
"page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding secondary servers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a server as a secondary, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in to the primary server with an account with the <emphasis>system "
"administrator</emphasis> role."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on the <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable> @ <replaceable>HOSTNAME</"
"replaceable> in the left upper corner."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Add new host</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in the host identification and user name that will be used to log in to "
"the server. You can assign a color to the machine. When the details are "
"complete, click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Verify a fingerprint on the server you want to add, if the fingerprint "
"matches or if you have not set up the SSH connection, click <guimenu>Accept "
"and connect</guimenu> to proceed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in the password and if needed check <guimenu>Automatic login</"
"guimenu> . Cockpit will generate a new SSH key for the user and next time "
"tou will be logged in automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "Logging into secondary servers directly"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can log in to any secondary server without logging in to the primary "
"server first. This solution can be useful when you do not have credentials "
"for the primary server. The primary server will be used as a bridge and you "
"will be connected to the secondary server using SSH."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To connect to the secondary server, expand <guimenu>Other options</guimenu> "
"on the login screen of the primary server. Fill in you user name, password "
"and the IP address of the secondary server. If you try to log in for the "
"first time, you are asked to verify the fingerprint, click <guimenu>Accept "
"and connect</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

